name: Bruntwood Park Orchard
short_description: Heritage fruit trees in a Victorian park.
description: A well-established community orchard featuring various apple and pear varieties near the Vinery.

name: Etherow Country Park Hazelnuts
description: Extensive hazel and sweet chestnut trees can be found along the valley sides and riverside trails.

name: Abney Hall Wild Garlic
short_description: Pungent spring greens in ancient woods.
description: The damp, shaded areas near the ponds and waterfalls are carpeted with wild garlic in spring.

name: Reddish Vale Elderberries
short_description: Abundant elder in the river valley.
description: Massive yields of elderflowers and berries along the Tame Valley Way and near the viaduct.

name: Incredible Edible Heaton Chapel
description: Community planters at Heaton Chapel station featuring herbs, fruit bushes, and seasonal veg.

name: Bramhall Park Walnuts
description: Mature walnut and sweet chestnut trees located within the woodland boundaries of the historic hall.

name: Merseyway Mall Herbs
description: Small planters in the pedestrianised centre featuring rosemary and chives.

name: Vernon Park Blackberries
description: The steep slopes leading down to the Goyt are packed with blackberries in late summer.

name: Lyme Park Sloes (Fringe)
description: The outer boundary walls and paths near Disley are excellent for sloe picking.

name: Goyt Valley Wild Garlic
description: The riverbanks between Marple and Stockport are prolific for wild garlic in April.

name: Woodbank Park Fruit Trees
description: Occasional apple trees remain from old estate plantings in the wilder parts of the park.

name: Marple Canal Rosehips
description: The Peak Forest Canal path is lined with wild rose and hawthorn bushes.

name: Incredible Edible Edgeley
description: Planters near the station entrance featuring kale, chives, and strawberries.

name: Heaton Norris Park Samphire (Inland Alternative)
description: Damp spots in the lower parklands often host wild celery and other riparian greens.

name: Happy Valley Beech Nuts
description: The local nature reserve has extensive beech and hazel groves perfect for autumn gathering.
